    <statement><div><h3 style="text-align:center;">Solve the following using reciprocals</h3>


<ol type="a">
<li><m> {6} \div \frac{{4}}{{6}} </m></li>
<li><m> {5}x = {30} </m></li>
<li><m> \frac{{2}}{{6}} x = {2} </m></li>
<li><m> {0.5} \div {0.4} </m></li>
</ol>


<p>
(a) <fillin characters="6" name="ans1"/>  <br/>
(b) <fillin characters="6" name="ans2"/>  <br/>
(c) <fillin characters="6" name="ans3"/>  <br/>
(d) <fillin characters="6" name="ans4"/>  
</p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>Dividing by a number is the same as multiplying by its reciprocal.</p>


<ol type="i">
<li>First, replace division by multiplication with the reciprocal.</li>
<li>Then simplify the expression.</li>
<li>Finding the value of<m>x</m> is like dividing the value after the equal sign by the reciprocal of the coefficient of <m>x</m> </li>
</ol>


<ol type="a">
<li><m> {6} \div \frac{{4}}{{6}} = {6} \times  \frac{{6}}{{4}}</m> <br/>
<m>= {9}</m>.<br/>
</li>
<li>To find the value of <m>x</m> in <m> {5}x = {30} </m>, first find the reciprocal of the <m>x</m> co-efficient then multiply it by the value after the equal sign. <br/>
<m>x= \frac{1}{ {5}} \times  {30}</m><br/>
Therefore,  <m>x = {6}</m>.<br/></li>
<li>Finding <m>x</m> in <m> \frac{{2}}{{6}} x = {2} </m>, we have:<br/>
 <m>x = \frac{{6}}{{2}} \times  {2} </m><br/>         
Hence, <m>x = {6}</m>.</li>
<li><m> {0.5} \div {0.4}  = \frac{{5}}{{10}} \div  \frac{{4}}{{10}}</m><br/>
   <m> = \frac{{5}}{{10}} \times \frac{{10}}{{4}}</m>   
<br/> <m>= {1.25}</m></li>
</ol></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>9</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>6</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>6</m></p></answer>
    <answer><p><m>1.25</m></p></answer>
